<section>
  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <p>
    Kim et al. present a catalog of black hole properties for 861 optically-classified Type-1 AGNs in the NEP-Wide field (z = 0.09-4.71) using multi-wavelength photometry (optical → mid-IR) and optical spectroscopy. They apply SED fitting to obtain extinction-corrected monochromatic MIR luminosities (rest-frame 3.4 and 4.6 μm) and measure broad emission line (BEL) FWHMs (C IV, Mg II, Hβ, Hα) from spectra. Combining LMIR with BEL FWHMs provides dust-insensitive single-epoch estimators for BH mass and bolometric luminosity.
  </p>

  <h3>Key findings</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Sample: 861 Type-1 AGNs (609 with reliable L3.4, 532 with reliable L4.6).</li>
    <li>Bolometric luminosities span Lbol ≈ 10^&#123;43.20&#125;-10^&#123;47.27&#125; erg s⁻¹.</li>
    <li>Black hole masses span MBH ≈ 10^&#123;7.29&#125;-10^&#123;9.67&#125; M⊙.</li>
    <li>Eddington ratios range ≈ 10^&#123;-2.74&#125;-10^&#123;-0.08&#125;.</li>
    <li>~34% of optically-classified Type-1 AGNs are dust-obscured; without extinction correction their Lbol would be underestimated.</li>
    <li>Provides a largely extinction-free catalog of BH properties across wide z for the NEP-Wide field — useful as fiducial estimates for SPHEREx and for AGN/host/environment studies.</li>
  </ul>

